# CURSOR-SKILLS - SQL (Postgres)

Aligned with skill [.cursor/skills/community/sql-postgres/SKILL.md](.cursor/skills/community/sql-postgres/SKILL.md).

## DDL and conventions

- CREATE TABLE with `IF NOT EXISTS`; explicit primary key; suitable types (UUID, TEXT, TIMESTAMPTZ, JSONB).
- snake_case names; COMMENT ON TABLE/COLUMN when it helps maintenance.

## Recommended patterns

- Table scripts: e.g. 001_create_tables.sql, 002_indexes_constraints.sql.
- DDL for integrations (logs, events, filters) in dedicated folders (db/, scripts/, code/).

## Best practices

- Idempotent scripts; TIMESTAMPTZ for dates; UUID when applicable.
- Document schema changes in docs or the module README.
